article.headline: Sparks show champions' compusure in OT
article.linkText: Mabika's touch in OT lifts Sparks past Monarchs
article.story:
SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Mwadi Mabika scored 19 points and
DeLisha Milton had 17 as the Los Angeles Sparks rallied Saturday to
defeat the Sacramento Monarchs 72-66 in overtime.

	   Mabika hit two 3-pointers in overtime and DeLisha Milton made
two shots from close range as the Sparks took a 67-59 lead with
2:34 left.

	   Tamecka Dixon helped bring the Sparks back late in regulation.
She made consecutive 3-pointers to conclude a 9-0 run, which tied
the game at 57 with 31.8 seconds remaining. She missed a jumper
with 2 seconds left that would have won the game.

	   "That's why we're the defending champs,'' Los Angeles coach
Michael Cooper said. "We know how to win.''

	   Dixon finished with 15 points for Los Angeles (7-1), which beat
Sacramento for the sixth straight time during the regular season.
Lisa Leslie, who fouled out in overtime, had 13 points and 11
rebounds and four blocks.

	   "We knew we were going to win in overtime,'' Dixon said. "It
was our game. We were confident in that situation.''

	   Ruthie Bolton scored 17 points, Kedra Holland-Corn had 12 points
and Ticha Penicheiro had 11 points and 10 assists for Sacramento
(1-5), which went scoreless in the final 3:08 of regulation.
Tangela Smith added nine points.

	   Sacramento appeared to take control of the game midway through
the second half, running off nine straight points. Bolton scored a
fast-break layup to start the run and Smith ended it by banking in
a shot from close range, putting the Monarchs ahead 44-35 with 8:38
left.

	   "We had the momentum, we had the game for the first 36
minutes,'' Bolton said. "We played the hardest, but we gave it to
them in the final two or three minutes.''

	   The Sparks shot 9-of-31 in the first half.

	   Sacramento played its fifth straight game without All-Star
center Yolanda Griffith, who has a bulging disc in her neck and is
expected to miss the next four weeks.
